<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-02-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="664" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d664">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 11513.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Bryan</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-02-01"><hi rend="italic">February 1,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Bryan reports that the King of Portugal and the Crown Prince have
                            been assassinated, being instantly killed by rifle shots on their
                            arrival from the country. Says the Queen and second son were saved.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>